Nature is a common Word  
That passes freely by -  
Yet in the silence of her Mood,  
The Echoes often try -  

To start a Bloom of Beauty  
That rumbles through the Dawn -  
If ever you may meet her,  
Let all your Griefs be drawn.

- Emily Dickinson
